            <abstract id="ref1" label="Abstract">The 6 volumes in the collection include orderly books, account books and diaries kept by James Burd, Sanuel Hunter, and others during the French and Indian War. The first two volumes in the collection, housed together, are an account book, a record of purchases of stockings, shoes, hats, knives, shirts, and sundries by soldiers, 19 February 21 May 1756; the second volume, Receipt Book, Camp at Shamokin, 1756 lists soldiers' receipts for pay, 21 July 22 October 1756.</abstract>
